gomodel:SYNGO_763  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper reports the identification of the GABA transporters GAT-3 and GAT-4.\n\nFigure 2 demonstrates the uptake Kinetics of 3H-GABA (2A), 3H-beta-alanine (2B), and 3H-taurine (3C) into Xenopus oocytes injected with synthetic mRNA of GAT3.\nThis suggests that GAT3 is the transporter of GABA, beta-alanine, and taurine.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has \"gamma-aminobutyric acid transmembrane transporter activity (GO:0015185)\" and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'neurotransmitter uptake (GO:0001504)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P31647] SynGO ID 768 (PMID:24368619, EM). Experimental description: 'Kinetics of GABA, and alanine, and taurine uptake into Xenopus oocytes injected with synthetic mRNA of GAT3'\nmRNA is isolated from mouse cDNA library." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2018-07-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_763" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
